<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 31 May 2026 13:11:07 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>四只稀有的关岛翠鸟雏鸟在弗吉尼亚州的设施中孵化，为少量已灭绝的野生鸟类增添了“极其宝贵”的资源</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/four-rare-guam-kingfisher-chicks-hatch-at-virginia-facility-making-an-incredibly-valuable-addition-to-the-small-population-of-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-180988863/</link><description>该物种也被称为“sihek”，在其故乡关岛被消灭，并被圈养存活。 2024年，环保人士在巴尔米拉环礁放生了一些鸟类，迄今为止它们一直繁衍生息</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 21:00:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/four-rare-guam-kingfisher-chicks-hatch-at-virginia-facility-making-an-incredibly-valuable-addition-to-the-small-population-of-extinct-in-the-wild-birds-180988863/</guid></item><item><title>这些具有 600 年历史的中国手术器械涂有早期局部麻醉剂——从有毒植物中精心提取</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-600-year-old-chinese-surgical-instruments-are-coated-in-an-early-local-anestheticcarefully-extracted-from-a-poisonous-plant-180988865/</link><description>研究人员表示，在手术过程中，麻醉剂溅到了铁剪刀和镊子上。它们是在明代医生墓中发现的</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 20:15:09 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-600-year-old-chinese-surgical-instruments-are-coated-in-an-early-local-anestheticcarefully-extracted-from-a-poisonous-plant-180988865/</guid></item><item><title>亚洲象 Happy 于布朗克斯动物园去世，享年 55 岁</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/happy-an-asian-elephant-who-demonstrated-that-her-species-might-be-self-aware-dies-at-55-at-the-bronx-zoo-180988861/</link><description>在大约 20 年前的研究报告中，Happy 似乎认出了镜子里的自己。后来，她成为一场失败诉讼的对象，该诉讼声称大象应该享有某些基本人权</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 18:23:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/happy-an-asian-elephant-who-demonstrated-that-her-species-might-be-self-aware-dies-at-55-at-the-bronx-zoo-180988861/</guid></item><item><title>艺术家利用彩色狗粮，将《蒙娜丽莎》、《尖叫》和《吻》变成人类最好的朋友可以欣赏的博物馆杰作</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/using-colorful-kibble-artists-turn-mona-lisa-the-scream-and-the-kiss-into-museum-masterpieces-that-mans-best-friend-can-appreciate-180988860/</link><description>来自新泽西州的姐妹们花了两个月的时间重新创作了著名的艺术品，同时也确保她们的狗不会进入可食用的艺术用品</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 18:16:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/using-colorful-kibble-artists-turn-mona-lisa-the-scream-and-the-kiss-into-museum-masterpieces-that-mans-best-friend-can-appreciate-180988860/</guid></item><item><title>希尔玛·阿夫·克林特 (Hilma af Klint) 是一位相信超凡脱俗的灵魂告诉她要画什么的神秘主义者。现在，她被认为是历史上第一位抽象艺术家之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-hilma-af-klint-the-occultist-who-believed-otherworldly-spirits-told-her-what-to-paint-now-shes-considered-one-of-historys-first-abstract-artists-180988859/</link><description>这位瑞典画家早在 1906 年就创作了大胆、充满活力的作品，比瓦西里·康定斯基等同时代人早了几年。法国举办的新展览庆祝她的“圣殿绘画”系列</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 16:08:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/meet-hilma-af-klint-the-occultist-who-believed-otherworldly-spirits-told-her-what-to-paint-now-shes-considered-one-of-historys-first-abstract-artists-180988859/</guid></item><item><title>霸王龙和其他可怕的掠食性恐龙拥有很小的手臂。科学家可能终于找到了原因</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tyrannosaurus-rex-and-other-terrifying-predatory-dinosaurs-had-itty-bitty-arms-scientists-may-have-finally-figured-out-why-180988803/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，某些兽脚亚目恐龙（两足，主要是食肉恐龙）的前肢缩小，作为其坚固头骨的进化权衡</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 15:53:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/tyrannosaurus-rex-and-other-terrifying-predatory-dinosaurs-had-itty-bitty-arms-scientists-may-have-finally-figured-out-why-180988803/</guid></item><item><title>在美国 250 岁生日之前，请参阅下周发行的纪念托马斯·杰斐逊和《独立宣言》的新季度</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-new-quarter-honoring-thomas-jefferson-and-the-declaration-of-independence-that-enters-circulation-next-week-ahead-of-americas-250th-birthday-180988843/</link><description>该设计是几种硬币面额之一，也是五枚新 25 枚硬币中的第三枚，专为该国五十周年纪念而设计</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 15:46:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-new-quarter-honoring-thomas-jefferson-and-the-declaration-of-independence-that-enters-circulation-next-week-ahead-of-americas-250th-birthday-180988843/</guid></item><item><title>在古塞浦路斯定居点发现的鸽子骨头表明我们与这些鸟类的关系比我们想象的要早</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/pigeon-bones-found-at-an-ancient-cyprus-settlement-reveal-that-our-relationship-with-these-birds-began-earlier-than-we-thought-180988791/</link><description>在普通鸽子被视为城市害虫之前，人们驯养它们并依靠它们获取肉、肥料、信息等。一项新研究表明，人类与这些有翅膀的生物一起生活了至少 3,400 年</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/pigeon-bones-found-at-an-ancient-cyprus-settlement-reveal-that-our-relationship-with-these-birds-began-earlier-than-we-thought-180988791/</guid></item><item><title>当乔治·华盛顿忙着在里面吃晚饭时，奥纳·法官逃离了奴隶制。现在，一幅新的壁画纪念了她的遗产</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ona-judge-escaped-from-slavery-while-george-washington-was-eating-dinner-inside-now-new-mural-honors-her-legacy-180988851/</link><description>新罕布什尔州朴次茅斯的这幅艺术品展示了法官 1796 年 5 月从费城出发抵达这座城市的情景。她一直是一名自由的女性，直到 1848 年去世</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 20:07:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/ona-judge-escaped-from-slavery-while-george-washington-was-eating-dinner-inside-now-new-mural-honors-her-legacy-180988851/</guid></item><item><title>比平常更小的蓝月亮将以月球奇观结束这个月。以下是关于完整微月的知识</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-smaller-than-usual-blue-moon-will-end-the-month-with-a-lunar-spectacle-heres-what-to-know-about-the-full-micromoon-180988854/</link><description>蓝月亮将是同月两次满月中的第二次，这种巧合大约每两年半才会发生一次。它也会比一般的满月显得更小、更暗</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 19:40:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-smaller-than-usual-blue-moon-will-end-the-month-with-a-lunar-spectacle-heres-what-to-know-about-the-full-micromoon-180988854/</guid></item><item><title>这位有影响力的超现实主义艺术家和女权主义者不仅仅是缪斯，在新的传记片和艺术展览中得到了应有的回报</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/leonora-carrington-is-no-mere-muse-this-influential-surrealist-artist-and-feminist-gets-her-due-in-a-new-biopic-and-art-exhibitions-180988844/</link><description>新电影《晨光中的利奥诺拉》颂扬了利奥诺拉·卡林顿的生活和工作。与此同时，弗洛伊德博物馆的一个展览首次展示了她在精神病院内创作的艺术品</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 19:26:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/leonora-carrington-is-no-mere-muse-this-influential-surrealist-artist-and-feminist-gets-her-due-in-a-new-biopic-and-art-exhibitions-180988844/</guid></item><item><title>研究称，随着气候变化，巨大的、破坏性的冰雹变得越来越普遍</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/giant-destructive-hail-is-becoming-more-common-with-climate-change-study-says-180988849/</link><description>随着大气变暖，出现像柚子那么大的冰雹的可能性正在增加</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 19:02:02 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/giant-destructive-hail-is-becoming-more-common-with-climate-change-study-says-180988849/</guid></item><item><title>得益于数百人进行恢复仪式的帮助，英格兰最著名的裸体巨人将再次发出白色光芒</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/englands-most-famous-naked-giant-will-glow-white-again-thanks-to-help-from-hundreds-of-people-performing-a-ritual-of-restoration-180988848/</link><description>英格兰南部 180 英尺高的 Cerne Abbas 巨人正在涂上一层新的粉笔</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 18:09:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/englands-most-famous-naked-giant-will-glow-white-again-thanks-to-help-from-hundreds-of-people-performing-a-ritual-of-restoration-180988848/</guid></item><item><title>切萨皮克湾的年轻蓝蟹多年来一直在神秘地减少。今年冬天，他们的人数有所增加。是什么推动了这些趋势？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/young-blue-crabs-have-been-mysteriously-dwindling-in-the-chesapeake-bay-for-years-this-winter-they-saw-a-boost-in-numbers-whats-driving-these-trends-180988839/</link><description>最近的一份报告详细介绍了自 2010 年以来幼年切萨皮克蓝蟹数量减少了 50%。然后，一项调查发现今年幼年甲壳类动物数量惊人地激增</description><pubDate>Thu, 28 May 2026 15:10:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/young-blue-crabs-have-been-mysteriously-dwindling-in-the-chesapeake-bay-for-years-this-winter-they-saw-a-boost-in-numbers-whats-driving-these-trends-180988839/</guid></item><item><title>你如何纪念倒下的树？在英国，一座声音雕塑将播放哈德良长城附近倒下的心爱梧桐树的“声音”</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-do-you-honor-a-fallen-tree-in-england-a-sound-sculpture-will-broadcast-the-voice-of-a-beloved-sycamore-felled-near-hadrians-wall-180988832/</link><description>“人民之树”还将把这棵树的木材和公众的档案记录融入一系列社区艺术作品中</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 20:51:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/how-do-you-honor-a-fallen-tree-in-england-a-sound-sculpture-will-broadcast-the-voice-of-a-beloved-sycamore-felled-near-hadrians-wall-180988832/</guid></item><item><title>美国宇航局公布了有关未来月球基地和为其建造奠定基础的任务的新细节</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-unveils-new-details-about-the-future-moon-base-and-the-missions-laying-the-groundwork-to-build-it-180988837/</link><description>前三个任务计划于今年发射。它们将涉及由包括蓝色起源在内的多家航空航天公司开发的月球着陆器，并运送科学仪器和月球车</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 20:47:37 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/nasa-unveils-new-details-about-the-future-moon-base-and-the-missions-laying-the-groundwork-to-build-it-180988837/</guid></item><item><title>欣赏令人惊叹的中世纪手稿，讲述亚瑟王的故事，以墨水和抛光黄金制成，即将拍卖</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-medieval-manuscript-telling-tales-of-king-arthur-in-ink-and-polished-gold-thats-headed-to-auction-180988835/</link><description>该手稿由一位技艺精湛的匿名艺术家于 1290 年至 1310 年间创作。它是仅有的三份私人拥有的通俗圣经循环手稿中最古老的一份</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 19:29:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-medieval-manuscript-telling-tales-of-king-arthur-in-ink-and-polished-gold-thats-headed-to-auction-180988835/</guid></item><item><title>1776 年，愤怒的纽约人怀着革命热情推倒了乔治三世的雕像。新展览让你也能做到</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-1776-angry-new-yorkers-tore-down-a-statue-of-george-iii-with-a-revolutionary-fervor-a-new-exhibition-lets-you-do-it-too-180988830/</link><description>纽约市在美国革命中发挥了关键作用。该博物馆通过文物、沉浸式环境和互动体验生动地展现了这座城市 18 世纪的历史</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 19:00:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-1776-angry-new-yorkers-tore-down-a-statue-of-george-iii-with-a-revolutionary-fervor-a-new-exhibition-lets-you-do-it-too-180988830/</guid></item><item><title>隐藏在林肯纪念堂下方的一座光彩夺目的新博物馆即将向公众开放。这是您可以期待的</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-illuminating-new-museum-hidden-beneath-the-lincoln-memorial-is-set-to-open-to-the-public-heres-what-you-can-expect-180988831/</link><description>林肯纪念堂地下博物馆的门票现已开放预订。当该景点于 6 月 25 日开放时，游客将从全新的角度欣赏这座华盛顿特区的地标建筑</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 17:21:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/an-illuminating-new-museum-hidden-beneath-the-lincoln-memorial-is-set-to-open-to-the-public-heres-what-you-can-expect-180988831/</guid></item><item><title>科学家利用人工智能重新设计微生物的机器，使其在没有生命关键成分的情况下也能发挥作用</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-used-ai-to-redesign-a-microbes-machinery-to-function-without-a-key-ingredient-of-life-180988802/</link><description>尽管研究人员没有创造出在没有关键构建模块的情况下也能发挥作用的完整细胞，但这些发现代表了合成生物学的一大进步，并让人们了解地球上最早的生物体可能是如何生活的。</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 15:46:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-used-ai-to-redesign-a-microbes-machinery-to-function-without-a-key-ingredient-of-life-180988802/</guid></item></channel></rss>